Cụ thể, các dòng code làm như sau:¶

  • import tensorflow as tf: import th vin TensorFlow
  • from tensorflow.keras import models, layers: import cc lp v m hnh t module keras trong TensorFlow
  • import matplotlib.pyplot as plt: import th vin matplotlib trc quan ha kt qu
  • import pandas as pd: import th vin pandas phn tch kt qu
  • import warnings: import module warnings qun l cnh bo trong qu trnh chy chng trnh
  • warnings.filterwarnings('ignore'): b qua tt c cc cnh bo xut hin trong qu trnh chy chng trnh. Cu lnh ny gip cho qu trnh hun luyn c thc hin m khng b gin on bi cc cnh bo khng quan trng.
  • Tm li, on code trn import cc th vin cn thit xy dng m hnh v phn tch kt qu, v thit lp cu hnh b qua cc cnh bo khng quan trng trong qu trnh chy chng trnh.

**Model constants

In [3]:
BATCH_SIZE = 32
IMAGE_SIZE = 256
CHANNELS=3
EPOCHS=20

  • BATCH_SIZE = 32: y l kch thc ca cc batch (tp cc mu d liu c x l cng lc) c s dng trong qu trnh hun luyn. Khi hun luyn m hnh, cc mu d liu s c chia thnh cc batch vi kch thc tng ng v c truyn vo m hnh cp nht trng s. Gi tr 32 l gi tr thng thng c s dng trong qu trnh hun luyn m hnh.

  • IMAGE_SIZE = 256: y l kch thc nh u vo (trong pixel) c s dng trong qu trnh hun luyn m hnh. Kch thc nh quyt nh phn gii ca nh u vo v nh hng n hiu sut ca m hnh. Kch thc 256x256 l kch thc thng thng c s dng trong cc bi ton phn loi nh.

  • CHANNELS = 3: y l s knh mu ca nh u vo, y gi tr l 3 tng ng vi nh RGB (Red, Green, Blue). Khi mt nh c a vo m hnh, nh s c phn chia thnh cc knh mu v mi knh mu s c x l c lp.

  • EPOCHS = 20: y l s ln m ton b tp d liu c hun luyn qua m hnh. Trong qu trnh hun luyn, m hnh s cp nht trng s ca mnh sau mi batch d liu c truyn qua. Sau khi ton b tp d liu c hun luyn qua m hnh, l mt epoch. Gi tr 20 y ni ln rng m hnh s c hun luyn qua ton b tp d liu 20 ln. S epoch cn s dng hun luyn m hnh ph thuc vo kch thc tp d liu, loi bi ton v m hnh c s dng.

def get_dataset_partitions_tf(df,
                         train_split=0.8, val_split=0.2, shuffle=True, shuffle_size=10000):
    assert (train_split  + val_split) == 1
    
    ds_size = len(df)
    
    if shuffle:
        df= df.shuffle(shuffle_size, seed=12)
    
    train_size = int(train_split * ds_size)
    val_size = int(val_split * ds_size)
    
    train_ds =df.take(train_size)    
    val_ds = df.skip(train_size).take(val_size)
    
    return train_ds, val_ds

  • Hm get_dataset_partitions_tf c s dng phn chia tp d liu thnh tp hun luyn v tp xc thc (validation set) da trn t l cho trc (train_split v val_split). Tng t l ca hai tp d liu ny phi bng 1.

  • u vo ca hm l dataframe (df), t l phn chia hun luyn (train_split), t l phn chia xc thc (val_split), c bt hoc tt chc nng xo trn (shuffle) v kch thc ca buffer c s dng xo trn (shuffle_size).

  • Hm tr v hai dataset: train_ds v val_ds. Hm s ly train_size bng cch nhn t l train_split vi kch thc ca dataframe. Tng t, hm s ly val_size bng cch nhn t l val_split vi kch thc ca dataframe. Sau , hm s s dng phng thc take v skip ca dataframe chia tp d liu thnh train_ds v val_ds.

train_ds = train_ds.cache().shuffle(1000).prefetch(buffer_size=tf.data.AUTOTUNE)
val_ds = val_ds.cache().shuffle(1000).prefetch(buffer_size=tf.data.AUTOTUNE)
dataset_test = dataset_test.cache().shuffle(1000).prefetch(buffer_size=tf.data.AUTOTUNE)

  • Cc dng code ny s dng cc phng thc ca tf.data.Dataset to ra cc b d liu hun luyn v kim tra, v lu tr cc b d liu ny trong b nh cache tng tc hun luyn.

  • C th, cc dng code ny c cc tc v sau:

  1. train_ds.cache(): lu tr cc mu d liu hun luyn trong b nh cache tng tc c d liu.
  2. train_ds.shuffle(1000): xo trn cc mu d liu hun luyn mi ln lp li trnh nh hng ca th t d liu n qu trnh hun luyn.
  3. train_ds.prefetch(buffer_size=tf.data.AUTOTUNE): ti cc mu d liu hun luyn vo b nh trc khi cn thit tng tc c d liu.
  • Tng t, cc b d liu kim tra v kim tra cng c lu tr trong b nh cache v c sp xp tng tc c d liu.

#keep size , normalize and data ogmantuation
data_scaling = tf.keras.Sequential([
  layers.experimental.preprocessing.Resizing(IMAGE_SIZE, IMAGE_SIZE),
  layers.experimental.preprocessing.Rescaling(1./255)
])
data_augmentation = tf.keras.Sequential([
  layers.experimental.preprocessing.RandomFlip("horizontal_and_vertical"),
  layers.experimental.preprocessing.RandomRotation(0.2),
  layers.experimental.preprocessing.RandomContrast(0.5),
  tf.keras.layers.experimental.preprocessing.RandomZoom(0.2),
  tf.keras.layers.experimental.preprocessing.RandomHeight(0.2),
  tf.keras.layers.experimental.preprocessing.RandomWidth(0.2)    
    
])
  • y l mt on code trong vic hun luyn m hnh my hc phn loi hnh nh c chua. C th, on code ny s dng th vin TensorFlow x l tp d liu hun luyn v kim tra, nh ngha v cu hnh mt s tham s cn thit cho vic hun luyn, to v p dng cc k thut data augmentation (m rng d liu), nh ngha hm chia tp d liu thnh cc phn tng ng vi tp hun luyn v tp validation, v cui cng l ti v s dng m hnh c hun luyn d on nhn ca cc hnh nh trong tp kim tra. C th, cc bc trong on code bao gm:
  1. Import cc th vin cn thit nh tensorflow, pandas v matplotlib.pyplot.
  2. nh ngha mt s hng s nh BATCH_SIZE, IMAGE_SIZE, CHANNELS v EPOCHS s dng trong vic hun luyn.
  3. Xc nh ng dn n cc th mc cha tp d liu hun luyn v kim tra bng bin df_train v df_test.
  4. S dng hm image_dataset_from_directory ca th vin tensorflow ti tp d liu hun luyn v kim tra t cc th mc xc nh trn v lu vo bin dataset_train v dataset_test tng ng. Hm ny cng thc hin mt s x l trn d liu nh shuffle v chia nh thnh cc batch hun luyn m hnh.
  5. Ly tn cc lp nhn t bin dataset_train v lu vo bin class_names.
  6. Hin th kch thc ca batch u tin trong tp d liu hun luyn v nhn ca cc hnh nh trong batch .
  7. V mt s hnh nh trong batch u tin ca tp d liu hun luyn v hin th nhn tng ng ca mi hnh nh.
  8. nh ngha hm get_dataset_partitions_tf chia tp d liu thnh tp hun luyn v tp validation.
  9. S dng hm get_dataset_partitions_tf chia tp d liu hun luyn thnh tp hun luyn v tp validation.
  10. Tin x l d liu bng cch s dng lp Rescaling chun ha gi tr pixel ca nh v khong [0, 1], v s dng cc k thut data augmentation
In [19]:
#now  let us apply data augmentation
train_ds = train_ds.map(
    lambda x, y: (data_augmentation(x, training=True), y)
).prefetch(buffer_size=tf.data.AUTOTUNE)

  • Trong on code trn, ang s dng phng thc map() p dng data_augmentation trn tp hun luyn train_ds. data_augmentation s dng cc lp x l nh to ra cc phin bn tng cng d liu cho nh, nhm gip m hnh hc c cc c trng quan trng hn v trnh overfitting.

  • Hm map() p dng mt hm lambda cho tng phn t ca train_ds, trong trng hp ny l lambda x, y: (data_augmentation(x, training=True), y). Hm ny s p dng data_augmentation ln nh u vo x v tr v mt cp (data_augmentation(x, training=True), y), trong training=True cho bit y l tp hun luyn.

  • Cui cng, dng prefetch() ti d liu cho b nh m trc khi cn thit, gip tng tc x l d liu cho m hnh.

In [20]:
input_shape = (BATCH_SIZE, IMAGE_SIZE, IMAGE_SIZE, CHANNELS)
n_classes = 10

model = models.Sequential([
    data_scaling,
  #  data_augmentation,
    layers.Conv2D(32, kernel_size = (3,3), activation='relu', input_shape=input_shape),
    layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)),
    layers.Conv2D(64,  kernel_size = (3,3), activation='relu'),
    layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)),
    layers.Conv2D(64,  kernel_size = (3,3), activation='relu'),
    layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)),
    layers.Conv2D(64, (3, 3), activation='relu'),
    layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)),
    layers.Conv2D(64, (3, 3), activation='relu'),
    layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)),
    layers.Conv2D(64, (3, 3), activation='relu'),
    layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)),
    layers.Flatten(),
    layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),
    layers.Dense(n_classes, activation='softmax'),
])

model.build(input_shape=input_shape)

Trong đoạn mã trên, đang xây dựng một mô hình mạng nơ-ron sâu (deep neural network) bằng thư viện keras của TensorFlow.¶

  • data_scaling l mt Sequential model cha hai lp nh hnh kch thc u vo v chun ho gi tr pixel v khong [0, 1].
  • n_classes l s lng cc lp (classes) cn phn loi tng u ra.
  • model l mt Sequential model cha cc lp cn thit hc cc c trng (features) ca nh u vo v phn loi chng vo cc lp tng ng.
  • Conv2D l lp tch chp hai chiu dng tm ra cc c trng ca nh.
  • MaxPooling2D l lp dng gim kch thc ca u vo bng cch ly gi tr ln nht trong cc vng ca s khng trng nhau ca nh.
  • Flatten l lp dng dui cc c trng tm c thnh mt vector a vo cc lp kt ni y (fully-connected layers) cui cng.
  • Dense l lp kt ni y vi s lng n v lp cui cng bng vi n_classes, v hm kch hot (activation function) lp cui cng l softmax, a ra xc sut ca mi nh ri vo tng lp.
  • Kch thc u vo ca m hnh l (BATCH_SIZE, IMAGE_SIZE, IMAGE_SIZE, CHANNELS) vi BATCH_SIZE l s lng nh trong mi ln hun luyn, IMAGE_SIZE l kch thc nh, CHANNELS l s knh mu ca nh (RGB l 3). Kch thc u ra ca m hnh l (BATCH_SIZE, n_classes). M hnh c xy dng vi input_shape l kch thc u vo.

Trong on code ny, ang s dng phng thc fit hun luyn m hnh vi d liu t dataset_train. Cc thng s ca phng thc c thit lp nh sau:

  • batch_size: kch thc ca mi batch d liu c s dng trong qu trnh hun luyn.
  • validation_data: tp d liu validation.
  • verbose: mc logging khi hun luyn m hnh.
  • epochs: s ln lp li qu trnh hun luyn. ### Kt qu ca qu trnh hun luyn c lu trong bin history.
In [24]:
scores =model.evaluate(dataset_test)

32/32 [==============================] - 5s 15ms/step - loss: 0.5027 - accuracy: 0.8750

  • y l cu lnh nh gi hiu sut ca m hnh trn tp d liu kim tra (test set). Cc nh gi ny c s dng nh gi kh nng ca m hnh trong vic phn loi nh trn tp d liu cha c hun luyn.

  • Cc nh gi c thc hin bng phng php "nh gi u ra" (output evaluation) v bao gm 2 thng s l "loss" v "accuracy". Thng s "loss" l mt s thc cho bit mc li ca m hnh trn tp d liu kim tra, cng thp th m hnh cng tt. Thng s "accuracy" l t l phn trm ca cc nh c phn loi ng trn tng s nh kim tra. Cng cao th m hnh cng tt.

  • Cu lnh scores = model.evaluate(dataset_test) s tr v gi tr ca loss v accuracy ca m hnh trn tp d liu kim tra v gn chng vo bin scores.

In [66]:
def predict_image(image_path, model):
    # c hnh nh t file v chuyn i thnh tensor
    img = tf.keras.preprocessing.image.load_img(image_path, target_size=(IMAGE_SIZE, IMAGE_SIZE))
    img_array = tf.keras.preprocessing.image.img_to_array(img)
    img_tensor = tf.keras.preprocessing.image.smart_resize(img_array, (IMAGE_SIZE, IMAGE_SIZE))
    img_tensor = tf.expand_dims(img_tensor, axis=0)

    # D on nhn ca hnh nh
    prediction = model.predict(img_tensor)
    predicted_class = np.argmax(prediction[0])

    return class_names[predicted_class]

  • y l mt hm d on nhn ca mt hnh nh bng cch s dng m hnh hun luyn. u vo ca hm l ng dn n tp hnh nh cn d on v m hnh hun luyn.

  • Hm bt u bng cch c hnh nh t tp v chuyn i n thnh tensor. Sau , tensor c m rng c mt chiu i din cho s lng nh ( y ch c mt nh), v sau c truyn vo m hnh d on nhn. Cui cng, hm tr v tn lp tng ng vi nhn c d on.
